  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: `geth version`\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\n#### Expected behaviour\n- [ ] when uploading from the fs, you can get a preset manifest so that you can force a mime type on a path when you upload from a directory. \n- [ ] The manifest can be used as an initial skeleton for an upload. \n- [ ] The skeleton can be used as restrictive or extensible (in the first case only path that are in the manifest are uploaded. Partial path with `*` suffix always designate that the all path continuations are legit.\n- [ ] optional warning for non-existing paths (you can edit mutable parts of an integrity protected site locally without downloading the entire data part. just let the manifest have entries (can point to mainifest)\n- [ ] all hashes are recalculated\n- [ ] links are redirects (followed or not) or not (followed)\n- [ ] integrity check vs credulous mode :\n  - [ ] credulous: if a hash not changed, do not reupload\n  - [ ] lazy: whenever new content check if root is retrievable\n  - [ ] normal: if changed follows through with audit if any intermediate is found\n  - [ ] paranoid: audit oevery node\n- [ ] sticky/non-sticky mime-types and status codes to enforce \n\nthe api should be:\n\n``` go\nfunc (self *Api) Upload(\"/path/to/content/\", &UploadOpts{\n  manifest-path: \"/path/to/skeleton\",   // root manifest skeleton\n  manifest: \".swarm-manifest\",           // optional relative overwrites per subdirectory \n  upload-manifests: true,                    // upload the optional manifests, so remains editable when downloaded\n upload-options-under: \".config\",        // to save this options json under\n integrity-check: \"normal\"                   // credulous|lazy|normal|paranoid\n published: \"mydomain/path/to/this\"   // \n```\n#### Actual behaviour\n\ncurrently no way to force a mime type to a content \n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n#### Backtrace\n\n```\n[backtrace]\n```\n",
